      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DR. LOUIS (2) showed good early burn and was there until turning but swamped late to finish 7th at this track in a Grade 5. Solid record here at the distance winning four races. Has winning claims on his best figures. SMOOTH TIGER (8) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (23.22) at Warragul over 400m. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to her name from 11 starts. Well placed and gets her chance. QUICK RESPONSE (3) finished well back at this track last time when a 8 length seventh (25.41) but scored four back at this track (24.93). Should be in this for a long way. DR. NATASHA (1) is worth including.",
